com.hds.hcpaw.fss.api

Class AnywhereFolderAPI

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hds.hcpaw.fss.api.AnywhereFolderAPI

  • public class AnywhereFolderAPI
extends java.lang.Object
    API for performing folder actions such as create and list the contents of a folder. These methods are implemented using the HCP Anywhere FSS API /fss/public/folder URIs.

    See the method AnywhereAPI.getFolderAPI() to obtain an instance of the AnywhereFolderAPI.

      • create

        public Entry create(AuthToken authToken,
                    java.lang.String path,
                    boolean createParents)
             throws AwUnsupportedApiVersionException,
                    java.io.IOException,
                    AnywhereException
        Creates a folder at the specified path. If the folder already exists, the operation returns the existing folder.
        Parameters:
        authToken - authentication token for the user performing the request
        path - path (including folder name) where the folder will be created
        createParents - if true, then any parent folders of path that do not already exist will be created. If false, then the operation will fail if any parent folders of path do not exist
        Returns:
        the created or already existing folder
        Throws:
        AwUnsupportedApiVersionException - if this method is not supported by the server due to the server's supported API versions
        AwNotFoundException - if the parent of path does not exist and createParents if false
        java.io.IOException
        AnywhereException

      • listEntries

        public FolderListing listEntries(AuthToken authToken,
                                 java.lang.String path,
                                 java.lang.String pageToken,
                                 int pageSize)
                          throws AwUnsupportedApiVersionException,
                                 java.io.IOException,
                                 AnywhereException
        Lists the contents (files and folders) of the specified folder, one "page" at a time. That is, this method returns up to as many entries as are specified in the pageSize parameter.

        This method should be called first with a null pageToken. Then, if there are more entries in the folder, subsequent calls should use the pageToken returned from the previous call.

        If the last page of entries is returned, then the returned FolderListing will contain a null pageToken.

        Parameters:
        authToken - authentication token for the user performing the request
        path - path (including folder name) to the folder
        pageToken - if null, the first page of entries are returned. To return the next page of entries, use the pageToken that was returned in the previous call
        pageSize - maximum number of entries to be returned
        Returns:
        a list of files and folders in the specified folder, up to the number of entries specified in the pageSize parameter. If there are more entries in the specified folder, a pageToken, which is used to retrieve the next page of entries, is also returned.
        Throws:
        AwUnsupportedApiVersionException - if this method is not supported by the server due to the server's supported API versions
        AwNotFoundException - if path does not exist or is not a folder
        java.io.IOException
        AnywhereException

      • listEntriesAtTime

        public FolderListing listEntriesAtTime(AuthToken authToken,
                                       java.lang.String path,
                                       java.lang.Long viewAtTime,
                                       java.lang.String pageToken,
                                       int pageSize)
                                throws AwUnsupportedApiVersionException,
                                       java.io.IOException,
                                       AnywhereException
        Lists the contents (files and folders) of the specified folder at a specified time, one "page" at a time. That is, this method returns up to as many entries as are specified in the pageSize parameter.

        This method should be called first with a null pageToken. Then, if there are more entries in the folder, subsequent calls should use the pageToken returned from the previous call.

        If the last page of entries is returned, then the returned FolderListing will contain a null pageToken.

        Parameters:
        authToken - authentication token for the user performing the request
        path - path (including folder name) to the folder
        viewAtTime - The point in time at which to list entries. Defaults to the current time if null.
        pageToken - if null, the first page of entries are returned. To return the next page of entries, use the pageToken that was returned in the previous call
        pageSize - maximum number of entries to be returned
        Returns:
        a list of files and folders in the specified folder, up to the number of entries specified in the pageSize parameter. If there are more entries in the specified folder, a pageToken, which is used to retrieve the next page of entries, is also returned.
        Throws:
        AwUnsupportedApiVersionException - if this method is not supported by the server due to the server's supported API versions
        AwNotFoundException - if path does not exist or is not a folder
        java.io.IOException

      • listEntriesAtTime

        public FolderListing listEntriesAtTime(AuthToken authToken,
                                       java.lang.String path,
                                       java.lang.Long viewAtTime,
                                       java.lang.String pageToken,
                                       int pageSize,
                                       FolderListingRequest.SortingCriterion sortingCriterion,
                                       FolderListingRequest.SortingDirection sortingDirection)
                                throws AwUnsupportedApiVersionException,
                                       java.io.IOException,
                                       AnywhereException
        Lists the contents (files and folders) of the specified folder at a specified time, one "page" at a time. That is, this method returns up to as many entries as are specified in the pageSize parameter.

        This method should be called first with a null pageToken. Then, if there are more entries in the folder, subsequent calls should use the pageToken returned from the previous call.

        If the last page of entries is returned, then the returned FolderListing will contain a null pageToken.

        Parameters:
        authToken - authentication token for the user performing the request
        path - path (including folder name) to the folder
        viewAtTime - The point in time at which to list entries. Defaults to the current time if null.
        pageToken - if null, the first page of entries are returned. To return the next page of entries, use the pageToken that was returned in the previous call
        pageSize - maximum number of entries to be returned
        sortingCriterion - How the results should be sorted (by NAME, SIZE, or MODIFY_DATE). Defaults to NAME. Folders always appear first.
        sortingDirection - In which direction the results should be presented (ASC for ascending order, DESC for descending order, based on the sorting criterion). Defaults to ASC.
        Returns:
        a list of files and folders in the specified folder, up to the number of entries specified in the pageSize parameter. If there are more entries in the specified folder, a pageToken, which is used to retrieve the next page of entries, is also returned.
        Throws:
        AwUnsupportedApiVersionException - if this method is not supported by the server due to the server's supported API versions
        AwNotFoundException - if path does not exist or is not a folder
        java.io.IOException
        AnywhereException
